content:
Use the Business Rules Engine to apply advanced logic and automate the decision-making process when onboarding an applicant.

Available in: Lightning Experience in Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions that have the Financial Services Cloud enabled

To create, update, and delete expression sets: Rule Engine Designer
To use decision tables in Business Rules Engine: Rules Engine Runtime

Decision matrices and expression sets are key components in the Business Rules Engine. Decision matrices are lookup tables that contain user-defined input and output columns.

When you enable the Sample Onboarding Application Template setting, you can access two prebuilt expression set templates.

Application Assessment Mapping: This template maps an application form to an assessment based on the value of the application form product.
Evaluate Party Profile Risk: This template determines the risk category for a party profile record based on the values of the Employment Industry, Employment Type, and Fund Source fields.

Set up a Decision Matrix and then build an expression set to automate the process of mapping an Application Form to an Assessment Type based on the Application Form Product selected by the applicant.
Set up a Decision Matrix and then build an expression set to automate the calculation of a risk category for a Party Profile record.
title: Setting Up Decision Matrices in Financial Services Cloud
